<para>
  <classname>UniformDriver</classname> objects are used as the
  <varname>time_stepper</varname> parameter in <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-AdvancedSolverMode"/> when solving a
  time-dependent problem with <link
  linkend="Section-Concepts-Mesh-Solvers">uniform time
  stepping</link>.  The <classname>UniformDriver</classname> uses the
  given <varname>stepper</varname> to take steps of size
  <varname>stepsize</varname> until the target time is reached.
</para>
<para>
  <classname>UniformDriver</classname> plays the same role in <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-AdvancedSolverMode"/> that <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-BasicUniformDriver"/> plays in <xref
  linkend="RegisteredClass-BasicSolverMode"/>.
</para>

